GhanaLSS: Not ready for DVC registration
=========================================

Current state
-------------
- data_scheme.yml defines: cluster_features, household_roster, food_acquired
- No dvc.yaml exists
- CLI materialize fails even for registered tables — multiple issues below

Bug fixes applied
-----------------
- Fixed imports: all scripts imported "from ghana import ..." but utility
  module is ghanalss.py. Updated all imports to "from ghanalss import ..."
- Fixed Makefile generic rule: referenced malawi.py (copy-paste error),
  now references ghanalss.py

Known issues blocking API/CLI
-----------------------------
1. Case sensitivity: Country class resolves paths as GHANALSS/ instead of
   GhanaLSS/ (e.g., /countries/GHANALSS/1988-89/../../_/categorical_mapping.org)
2. Missing categorical_mapping.org at expected path for mapping.py
3. No wave-level other_features.py or household_characteristics.py scripts

Unregistered country-level aggregator scripts
----------------------------------------------
- household_characteristics.py — no wave-level scripts exist
- other_features.py — no wave-level scripts exist
- food_prices_quantities_and_expenditures.py — produces food_expenditures,
  food_prices, food_quantities from food_acquired; depends on
  other_features.parquet via Makefile chain

Wave-level scripts
------------------
food_acquired.py in all 7 waves; mapping.py in waves 1987-88 through 1998-99.

Next steps
----------
1. Fix case-sensitivity issue in Country class path resolution for GhanaLSS
2. Create wave-level other_features.py and household_characteristics.py
3. Then register all tables in data_scheme.yml and create dvc.yaml
